  "description": "A balanced South Indian lunch bowl where legumes, vegetables, and whole grains carry the dish instead of excess fat. Paruppu Rasam with Red Rice brings a distinct structure, seasoning pattern, and grain-legume balance to the table.",
  "preparation": "",
  "cooking_steps": [
    "Combine tamarind water, tomato, vegetable element, salt, and 500 ml water in a pot and simmer on medium heat for 8 minutes.",
    "Add the cooked pulse and the crushed pepper-cumin-garlic mixture and simmer 4 minutes more until the raw garlic smell disappears.",
    "Temper mustard and curry leaves in oil over medium heat and pour over the rasam. Switch off the heat as soon as the rasam foams lightly at the edges.",
    "Rest 2 minutes, then ladle over the cooked grain."
  ],
